# Leash — Robot Harness

## Product

A Rust harness runtime for robot control. DimOS-inspired parity surface built Rust-first, MCP-first, simulation-safe. Exposes robot hardware through a typed module graph, CLI/HTTP server, and MCP stdio interface. LLM agents command physical robots through composable blueprints. Feature-gated hardware adapters (Waveshare UGV first, then quadrupeds, humanoids, drones, arms). Safety gates at every layer. Replay and simulation workflows require zero hardware.

**Product benchmark**: `dimensionalOS/dimos` (3.5k stars, Python). Leash targets the same operating surface — blueprints, module graph, MCP tooling, replay, transport abstraction, telemetry — in Rust with stronger safety defaults.

## What the User Sees

### Interface: CLI

```
$ leash serve --http 127.0.0.1:9000
[leash] module graph loaded: 5 modules, 12 streams
[leash] blueprints: ugv-nav, sim-replay, agent-debug
[leash] safety gates: motor-limit, estop, watchdog
[leash] HTTP server listening on 127.0.0.1:9000
[leash] MCP stdio ready
[leash] replay buffer: 0s (idle)
```

### Interface: MCP (LLM Agent)

```
Tool: leash_module_list()
Tool: leash_module_status(name)
Tool: leash_blueprint_start(name)
Tool: leash_motor(direction, speed, duration_ms)
Tool: leash_sensor(sensor_name)
Tool: leash_estop()
Tool: leash_replay_start(session_id)
Tool: leash_telemetry(stream_name)
```

### Interface: Module Graph (Dev)

```
$ leash graph list
MODULE          STATE     INPUTS          OUTPUTS
motor_ctrl      running   cmd_vel         odom, health
lidar_proc      running   raw_scans       pointcloud
nav_planner     running   pointcloud,odom path, cmd_vel
safety_gate     running   cmd_vel, estop  cmd_vel_safe
telemetry_out   running   *               json_stream
```

## User Stories

| ID | Story | Pri | Acceptance |
|----|-------|-----|------------|
| LS-01 | Operator starts harness with `leash serve` | P0 | HTTP + MCP endpoints respond |
| LS-02 | LLM agent commands rover motor via MCP | P0 | Rover moves; safety gate enforces limits |
| LS-03 | Operator hits estop via CLI | P0 | All motors halt within 100ms |
| LS-04 | Integrator adds new robot bridge | P1 | Existing bridge clients work unchanged |
| LS-05 | Hardware vendor contributes UGV adapter | P1 | Feature-gated, compiles only when enabled |
| LS-06 | CI smoke-tests MCP, HTTP, and safety gates | P1 | `cargo test --features smoke` passes |
| LS-07 | Package published to crates.io | P2 | `cargo install leash` works |
| LS-08 | Binary release on GitHub | P2 | Download + run, no Rust toolchain needed |
| LS-09 | Developer defines a module with typed inputs/outputs | P0 | Module appears in `leash graph list` with correct streams |
| LS-10 | Operator runs a blueprint in sim mode | P0 | Full nav pipeline executes without hardware |
| LS-11 | Developer replays a recorded session | P1 | Replay reproduces exact telemetry stream |
| LS-12 | Operator views live telemetry graph | P1 | `leash telemetry` shows real-time stream data |
| LS-13 | Integrator bridges external transport | P2 | Cross-process module communicates over TCP |
